data.content:
Here are the three EF Core 10 breaking changes affecting your code and how to fix each:

---

## 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now accepts a regular lambda

The API changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Action<...>`. Your complex expression tree construction no longer compiles and can be **dramatically simplified**:

```csharp
// .NET 10 fix — simple lambda with conditionals
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda`, `Expression.Call`, or manual tree manipulation needed.

---

## 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified/use full path

Two changes hit you:

- **Same-named properties across complex types** (e.g., `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) now get a numeric suffix to disambiguate.
- **Nested complex types** use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

Both generate migrations that rename columns. **Fix:** pin column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// Nested example
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, a =>
        {
            a.Property(x => x.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

## 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (redacted SQL for safe logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText) // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Add the parameter to every method in the interface implementation (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
